## Ä°nteraktiv Hesablama:
calculate_rasch_scenarios <- function() {
  scenarios <- expand.grid(
    theta = c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2),
    beta = c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2)
  )
  
  scenarios$difference <- scenarios$theta - scenarios$beta
  scenarios$probability <- rasch_prob(scenarios$theta, scenarios$beta)
  scenarios$interpretation <- ifelse(scenarios$probability > 0.75, "Ã‡ox yÃ¼ksÉ™k",
                                   ifelse(scenarios$probability > 0.50, "YÃ¼ksÉ™k",
                                         ifelse(scenarios$probability > 0.25, "AÅŸaÄŸÄ±", "Ã‡ox aÅŸaÄŸÄ±")))
  
  return(scenarios)
}

scenarios_result <- calculate_rasch_scenarios()

## 5     Common item linking       Scale building

# Specific Objectivity demonstration
cat("\n=== SPECÄ°FÄ°K OBYEKTÄ°VLÄ°K DEMONSTRASÄ°YASI ===\n\n")
## 
## === SPECÄ°FÄ°K OBYEKTÄ°VLÄ°K DEMONSTRASÄ°YASI ===
demonstrate_objectivity <- function() {
  set.seed(12345)
  
  # Create two person groups with different ability distributions
  n_persons_low <- 100
  n_persons_high <- 100
  
  theta_low <- rnorm(n_persons_low, mean = -1, sd = 0.8)  # Lower ability group
  theta_high <- rnorm(n_persons_high, mean = 1, sd = 0.8)  # Higher ability group
  
  # Create items with different difficulties
  n_items <- 10
  beta_items <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  # Generate response data for both groups
  generate_rasch_data <- function(theta_vec, beta_vec) {
    n_p <- length(theta_vec)
    n_i <- length(beta_vec)
    data <- matrix(NA, n_p, n_i)
    
    for(i in 1:n_p) {
      for(j in 1:n_i) {
        prob <- rasch_prob(theta_vec[i], beta_vec[j])
        data[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
      }
    }
    return(data)
  }
  
  data_low <- generate_rasch_data(theta_low, beta_items)
  data_high <- generate_rasch_data(theta_high, beta_items)
  
  # Calculate item difficulties from each group separately
  calc_item_difficulties <- function(data) {
    item_means <- colMeans(data, na.rm = TRUE)
    # Convert proportion correct to logit (approximate)
    item_difficulties <- -qlogis(item_means)
    return(item_difficulties)
  }
  
  beta_est_low <- calc_item_difficulties(data_low)
  beta_est_high <- calc_item_difficulties(data_high)
  
  cat("Item Difficulty Estimates from Different Groups:\n")
  difficulty_comparison <- data.frame(
    Item = 1:n_items,
    True_Beta = round(beta_items, 2),
    Est_Low_Group = round(beta_est_low, 2),
    Est_High_Group = round(beta_est_high, 2),
    Difference = round(abs(beta_est_low - beta_est_high), 3)
  )
  
  print(difficulty_comparison)
  
  # Correlation between estimates
  cor_difficulties <- cor(beta_est_low, beta_est_high)
  mean_difference <- mean(abs(beta_est_low - beta_est_high))
  
  cat("\nObjectivity Assessment:\n")
  cat("Correlation between group estimates:", round(cor_difficulties, 3), "\n")
  cat("Mean absolute difference:", round(mean_difference, 3), "\n")
  
  if(cor_difficulties > 0.90 && mean_difference < 0.5) {
    objectivity_assessment <- "Strong objectivity - item difficulties stable"
  } else if(cor_difficulties > 0.80) {
    objectivity_assessment <- "Moderate objectivity - some group dependency"
  } else {
    objectivity_assessment <- "Weak objectivity - group-dependent estimates"
  }
  
  cat("Assessment:", objectivity_assessment, "\n\n")
  
  # Plot comparison
  if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
    plot_data <- data.frame(
      Low_Group = beta_est_low,
      High_Group = beta_est_high,
      Item = factor(1:n_items)
    )
    
    obj_plot <- ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = Low_Group, y = High_Group)) +
      geom_point(aes(color = Item), size = 3) +
      geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, linetype = "dashed", color = "red") +
      labs(title = "Specific Objectivity: Item Difficulties Across Groups",
           x = "Difficulty Estimate (Low Ability Group)",
           y = "Difficulty Estimate (High Ability Group)") +
      theme_minimal() +
      annotate("text", x = min(beta_est_low), y = max(beta_est_high),
               label = paste("r =", round(cor_difficulties, 3)), size = 4)
    
    print(obj_plot)
  }
  
  return(list(
    correlation = cor_difficulties,
    mean_diff = mean_difference,
    assessment = objectivity_assessment
  ))
}

# Simulate Rasch data with known fit patterns
simulate_rasch_fit_scenarios <- function() {
  set.seed(54321)
  n_persons <- 200
  n_items <- 15
  
  # Person abilities
  theta <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)
  
  # Item difficulties
  beta <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  # Scenario 1: Good fit (pure Rasch)
  data_good <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- rasch_prob(theta[i], beta[j])
      data_good[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  # Scenario 2: Underfit (extra randomness)
  data_underfit <- data_good
  # Add noise to some responses
  noise_indices <- sample(1:(n_persons * n_items), n_persons * n_items * 0.15)
  data_underfit[noise_indices] <- 1 - data_underfit[noise_indices]
  
  # Scenario 3: Overfit (too deterministic - Guttman-like)
  data_overfit <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    person_score <- sum(theta[i] > beta)  # Deterministic scoring
    # Make it slightly probabilistic
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      if(j <= person_score) {
        data_overfit[i, j] <- ifelse(runif(1) < 0.95, 1, 0)
      } else {
        data_overfit[i, j] <- ifelse(runif(1) < 0.05, 1, 0)
      }
    }
  }
  
  colnames(data_good) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  colnames(data_underfit) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  colnames(data_overfit) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  
  return(list(
    good_fit = data_good,
    underfit = data_underfit, 
    overfit = data_overfit,
    theta = theta,
    beta = beta
  ))
}

# Manual fit calculation (simple version)
calculate_simple_fit <- function(data) {
  n_persons <- nrow(data)
  n_items <- ncol(data)
  
  # Person total scores
  person_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  theta_est <- scale(person_scores)[, 1]  # Simple ability estimate
  
  # Item difficulties (simple estimate)
  item_means <- colMeans(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  beta_est <- -qlogis(pmax(0.01, pmin(0.99, item_means)))  # Avoid extreme values
  
  # Calculate expected probabilities
  expected_probs <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      expected_probs[i, j] <- rasch_prob(theta_est[i], beta_est[j])
    }
  }
  
  # Residuals
  residuals <- data - expected_probs
  
  # Simple outfit (unweighted mean square)
  outfit_stats <- numeric(n_items)
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    item_residuals <- residuals[, j]
    item_expected <- expected_probs[, j]
    
    # Variance of each response
    variances <- item_expected * (1 - item_expected)
    
    # Outfit = sum of squared standardized residuals / df
    outfit_stats[j] <- sum((item_residuals^2) / variances, na.rm = TRUE) / 
                       sum(!is.na(item_residuals))
  }
  
  return(list(
    theta_est = theta_est,
    beta_est = beta_est,
    outfit = outfit_stats,
    expected_probs = expected_probs,
    residuals = residuals
  ))
}

6 R-dÉ™ Rasch Analizi: eRm Paketi

6.1 eRm Paketi ilÉ™ Comprehensive Rasch Analysis

cat("=== R-DÆ RASCH ANALÄ°ZÄ°: eRm PAKETÄ° ===\n\n")
## === R-DÆ RASCH ANALÄ°ZÄ°: eRm PAKETÄ° ===
# eRm paketi ilÉ™ Rasch analizi
perform_erm_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== eRm RASCH ANALÄ°ZÄ°:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(eRm, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("eRm paketi mÃ¶vcud deyil. Manual analiz aparÄ±lÄ±r.\n")
    return(perform_manual_rasch_analysis(data, data_name))
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    # 1. Fit Rasch model
    cat("Rasch model fitting...\n")
    rasch_model <- RM(data)
    
    # 2. Model summary
    cat("\nModel Summary:\n")
    model_summary <- summary(rasch_model)
    print(model_summary)
    
    # 3. Item parameters
    cat("\nItem Parameters:\n")
    item_params <- -rasch_model$etapar  # eRm uses negative parameterization
    names(item_params) <- colnames(data)
    
    item_param_table <- data.frame(
      Item = names(item_params),
      Difficulty = round(item_params, 3),
      Interpretation = ifelse(item_params < -1, "Asan",
                             ifelse(item_params < 0, "Orta-asan", 
                                   ifelse(item_params < 1, "Orta-Ã§É™tin", "Ã‡É™tin")))
    )
    
    print(item_param_table)
    
    # 4. Person parameters
    cat("\nPerson Parameters (first 10):\n")
    person_params <- person.parameter(rasch_model)
    theta_estimates <- person_params$thetapar
    
    person_summary <- data.frame(
      Person = 1:min(10, length(theta_estimates)),
      Raw_Score = rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)[1:min(10, nrow(data))],
      Theta_Estimate = round(theta_estimates[1:min(10, length(theta_estimates))], 3),
      SE = round(person_params$se.theta[1:min(10, length(theta_estimates))], 3)
    )
    
    print(person_summary)
    
    # 5. Item fit statistics
    cat("\nItem Fit Statistics:\n")
    item_fit <- itemfit(person_params)
    
    fit_table <- data.frame(
      Item = colnames(data),
      Outfit = round(item_fit$i.outfitMSQ, 3),
      Outfit_t = round(item_fit$i.outfitZ, 2),
      Infit = round(item_fit$i.infitMSQ, 3),
      Infit_t = round(item_fit$i.infitZ, 2),
      Fit_Status = ifelse(item_fit$i.outfitMSQ > 1.3 | item_fit$i.outfitMSQ < 0.7, 
                         "Misfit", "Fit")
    )
    
    print(fit_table)
    
    # 6. Person fit statistics
    cat("\nPerson Fit Statistics (sample):\n")
    person_fit <- personfit(person_params)
    
    misfit_persons <- sum(person_fit$p.outfitMSQ > 1.3 | person_fit$p.outfitMSQ < 0.7, na.rm = TRUE)
    total_persons <- sum(!is.na(person_fit$p.outfitMSQ))
    misfit_rate <- round(100 * misfit_persons / total_persons, 1)
    
    cat("Misfitting persons:", misfit_persons, "/", total_persons, "(", misfit_rate, "%)\n")
    
    # 7. Wright Map (Person-Item map)
    cat("\nWright Map (Person-Item Distribution):\n")
    if(require(lattice, quietly = TRUE)) {
      tryCatch({
        plotPImap(rasch_model, main = paste("Wright Map -", data_name))
      }, error = function(e) {
        cat("Wright map Ã§É™kilÉ™ bilmÉ™di\n")
      })
    }
    
    # 8. Item Characteristic Curves
    cat("\nItem Characteristic Curves:\n")
    tryCatch({
      plotICC(rasch_model, item.subset = 1:min(6, ncol(data)), 
              main = paste("ICCs -", data_name))
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("ICC plots Ã§É™kilÉ™ bilmÉ™di\n")
    })
    
    # 9. Model tests
    cat("\nModel Tests:\n")
    
    # Andersen LR test
    tryCatch({
      lr_test <- LRtest(rasch_model, splitcr = "median")
      cat("Andersen LR Test:\n")
      cat("  LR statistic:", round(lr_test$LR, 3), "\n")
      cat("  p-value:", round(lr_test$pvalue, 4), "\n")
      
      if(lr_test$pvalue < 0.05) {
        cat("  â†’ Model fit problematic\n")
      } else {
        cat("  â†’ Model fit acceptable\n")
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("LR test aparÄ±la bilmÉ™di\n")
    })
    
    # 10. Reliability/Separation
    cat("\nSeparation vÉ™ Reliability:\n")
    person_separation <- person_params$betapar
    if(!is.null(person_separation)) {
      person_reliability <- var(person_separation) / (var(person_separation) + mean(person_params$se.theta^2))
      cat("Person separation reliability:", round(person_reliability, 3), "\n")
    }
    
    return(list(
      model = rasch_model,
      item_params = item_params,
      person_params = theta_estimates,
      item_fit = fit_table,
      misfit_rate = misfit_rate
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("eRm analysis xÉ™tasÄ±:", e$message, "\n")
    return(perform_manual_rasch_analysis(data, data_name))
  })
}

# Manual Rasch analysis (eRm olmayanda)
perform_manual_rasch_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MANUAL RASCH ANALÄ°ZÄ°:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  # Basic statistics
  n_persons <- nrow(data)
  n_items <- ncol(data)
  
  cat("Basic Statistics:\n")
  cat("Persons:", n_persons, "\n")
  cat("Items:", n_items, "\n")
  
  # Raw scores
  person_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  item_scores <- colSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  cat("Score ranges:\n")
  cat("Person scores:", min(person_scores), "-", max(person_scores), "\n")
  cat("Item scores:", min(item_scores), "-", max(item_scores), "\n")
  
  # Simple item difficulties (proportion-based)
  item_props <- colMeans(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  item_difficulties <- -qlogis(pmax(0.01, pmin(0.99, item_props)))
  
  cat("\nItem Difficulties (logit):\n")
  item_table <- data.frame(
    Item = colnames(data),
    Proportion = round(item_props, 3),
    Difficulty = round(item_difficulties, 3),
    Interpretation = ifelse(item_difficulties < -1, "Asan",
                           ifelse(item_difficulties < 0, "Orta-asan",
                                 ifelse(item_difficulties < 1, "Orta-Ã§É™tin", "Ã‡É™tin")))
  )
  
  print(item_table)
  
  # Simple reliability estimate
  cronbach_alpha <- NA
  if(require(psych, quietly = TRUE)) {
    alpha_result <- alpha(data, check.keys = FALSE)
    cronbach_alpha <- alpha_result$total$std.alpha
    cat("\nCronbach's Alpha:", round(cronbach_alpha, 3), "\n")
  }
  
  return(list(
    item_difficulties = item_difficulties,
    person_scores = person_scores,
    alpha = cronbach_alpha
  ))
}

## === TAM PAKETÄ° Ä°LÆ RASCH ANALÄ°ZÄ° ===
# TAM paketi ilÉ™ analiz
perform_tam_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== TAM RASCH ANALÄ°ZÄ°:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(TAM, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("TAM paketi mÃ¶vcud deyil.\n")
    return(NULL)
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    # 1. Fit Rasch model
    cat("TAM Rasch model fitting...\n")
    tam_model <- tam.mml(resp = data, constraint = "items")
    
    # 2. Model summary
    cat("\nModel Fit Summary:\n")
    cat("Log-Likelihood:", round(tam_model$deviance / -2, 2), "\n")
    cat("Number of parameters:", tam_model$ic$Npars, "\n")
    cat("AIC:", round(tam_model$ic$AIC, 2), "\n")
    cat("BIC:", round(tam_model$ic$BIC, 2), "\n")
    
    # 3. Item parameters
    cat("\nItem Parameters:\n")
    item_params <- tam_model$xsi
    item_param_df <- data.frame(
      Item = colnames(data),
      Difficulty = round(item_params, 3),
      SE = round(sqrt(diag(tam_model$xsi.fixed.estimated)), 3)
    )
    
    print(head(item_param_df, 10))
    
    # 4. Person parameters
    cat("\nPerson Parameters (WLE estimates):\n")
    person_wle <- tam.wle(tam_model)
    
    person_summary_tam <- data.frame(
      Person = 1:min(10, nrow(data)),
      Raw_Score = rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)[1:min(10, nrow(data))],
      WLE_Estimate = round(person_wle$theta[1:min(10, nrow(data))], 3),
      SE = round(person_wle$error[1:min(10, nrow(data))], 3)
    )
    
    print(person_summary_tam)
    
    # 5. Model fit indices
    cat("\nModel Fit Indices:\n")
    
    # Item fit
    item_fit_tam <- tam.fit(tam_model)
    if(!is.null(item_fit_tam)) {
      cat("Item fit statistics hesablandÄ±\n")
      
      # Display some fit statistics
      fit_summary <- data.frame(
        Statistic = c("Mean Outfit", "SD Outfit", "Items > 1.3", "Items < 0.7"),
        Value = c(
          round(mean(item_fit_tam$itemfit$Outfit, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
          round(sd(item_fit_tam$itemfit$Outfit, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
          sum(item_fit_tam$itemfit$Outfit > 1.3, na.rm = TRUE),
          sum(item_fit_tam$itemfit$Outfit < 0.7, na.rm = TRUE)
        )
      )
      
      print(fit_summary)
    }
    
    # 6. Person reliability
    wle_reliability <- person_wle$WLE.rel
    eap_reliability <- tam_model$EAP.rel
    
    cat("\nReliability Indices:\n")
    cat("WLE Reliability:", round(wle_reliability, 3), "\n")
    cat("EAP Reliability:", round(eap_reliability, 3), "\n")
    
    # 7. Information function
    cat("\nTest Information Function:\n")
    theta_seq <- seq(-3, 3, by = 0.5)
    test_info <- tam.testlet(tam_model, theta = theta_seq)
    
    info_summary <- data.frame(
      Theta = theta_seq,
      Information = round(test_info$test_info, 2),
      SE = round(1 / sqrt(test_info$test_info), 3)
    )
    
    print(head(info_summary, 7))
    
    return(list(
      model = tam_model,
      item_params = item_params,
      person_wle = person_wle,
      wle_reliability = wle_reliability,
      eap_reliability = eap_reliability
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("TAM analysis xÉ™tasÄ±:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# TAM analizi
tam_result <- perform_tam_analysis(scenarios$good_fit, "Good Fit Data")

# Manual separation calculation
calculate_separation_indices <- function(data) {
  # Person separation
  person_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  n_items <- ncol(data)
  
  # Convert raw scores to theta estimates (approximate)
  props <- person_scores / n_items
  props_adj <- pmax(0.01, pmin(0.99, props))  # Avoid extreme values
  theta_est <- qlogis(props_adj)
  
  # Person separation calculation
  theta_var <- var(theta_est, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # Approximate measurement error
  # For Rasch, SE decreases with extreme scores
  measurement_errors <- sqrt(1 / (n_items * props_adj * (1 - props_adj)))
  mean_error_var <- mean(measurement_errors^2, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  person_separation <- sqrt(max(0, theta_var - mean_error_var) / mean_error_var)
  person_reliability <- theta_var / (theta_var + mean_error_var)
  
  # Item separation
  item_scores <- colSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  n_persons <- nrow(data)
  
  # Item difficulty estimates
  item_props <- item_scores / n_persons
  item_props_adj <- pmax(0.01, pmin(0.99, item_props))
  beta_est <- -qlogis(item_props_adj)
  
  beta_var <- var(beta_est, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # Item measurement error (approximate)
  item_errors <- sqrt(1 / (n_persons * item_props_adj * (1 - item_props_adj)))
  mean_item_error_var <- mean(item_errors^2, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  item_separation <- sqrt(max(0, beta_var - mean_item_error_var) / mean_item_error_var)
  item_reliability <- beta_var / (beta_var + mean_item_error_var)
  
  return(list(
    person_separation = person_separation,
    person_reliability = person_reliability,
    item_separation = item_separation,
    item_reliability = item_reliability,
    theta_estimates = theta_est,
    beta_estimates = beta_est
  ))
}

    } else {
      person_interp <- "Poor (<1 stratum)"
    }
    
    cat("Person Separation Quality:", person_interp, "\n")
  }
